cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper proposes a method for automatically searching for loss functions during the training process in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The method also uses reinforcement learning, which is commonly used in the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a search space and optimization framework, which are also common topics in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method compared to existing hand-crafted loss functions, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on benchmark datasets, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.SD (Software Engineering).
